<p>
    <strong>From the college:</strong>
    <i>Students may be awarded credit for the Advanced Placement (AP) program of the College Board if a score of three or higher is achieved on the examination provided by the AP program. Scores must be sent directly from the College Board to the Records Office at Southern State.</i>
    <br/>
    For more information, <a href="http://www.sscc.edu/catalog.pdf" target="_blank" title="Opens a new window">view the credit policy on this college's website</a>.
